One person has been shot and killed in what appeared to be a hit on Tuesday afternoon in Johannesburg. Paramedics Emer-G-Med said the shooting happened on the corner of President Fouché and Malibongwe Drive in Randburg‚ and two people were injured. Photographs of the scene‚ shared on social media‚ showed a BMW X5 riddled with bullet holes. The incident took place at about 2pm. This is a developing story.